  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Users are frequently downloading the source distributions rather than the binaries from our release notes on GitHub. The source bundles appear under \"Assets\", which draws the eye, and I've made the same mistake at least once.\r\n\r\nCan we remove these, or rename them something like \"Do Not Download\", or add the binaries into the assets list, or anything to prevent this from happening?\r\n\r\nIf users actually want the source, they can easily git clone it.",
